description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Registered A&amp;E Nurse Band 5 &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Pennine Acute Trust&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: Fairfield Hospital&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pay rates:&lt;strong&gt; Day: &lt;/strong&gt;£23.4&lt;strong&gt; – Night/Saturday: &lt;/strong&gt;£30.42 &lt;strong&gt;Sunday/Bank Holiday: &lt;/strong&gt;£37.44&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Various shift patterns available. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Would you like to be part of a ‘Respectful, Caring, Responsible &amp; Committed Trust’ that values employees and recognises the hard work and dedication that everyone demonstrates day in, day out?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are looking to expand the Bank at The Pennine Trust, and are interested to hear from any A&amp;E trained registered nurses that may be able to spare extra time, from one shift per month to full time hours, we have shifts available to accommodate. We pay weekly!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We are looking for enthusiastic and highly motivated Band 5 Registered Nurses to work Bank shifts in in the A&amp;E &amp; Emergency Department at Fairfield hospital&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will work within a team to promote and provide high quality care and have excellent interpersonal communication skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be proficient in the delivery of care to patients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure safe administration of drugs in accordance with NMC and CHS policies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure accurate records are kept in accordance with CHS policy and NMC guidelines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In order to apply for a post, you &lt;strong&gt;must&lt;/strong&gt; have a minimum of 6 months experience in a similar role held within the last 2 years and be NMC registered.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We’re committed to giving you more flexibility and control over your working life. By joining the NHSP bank you’ll gain access to the best choice of available shifts.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return for your hard work and your professional, caring and reliable service you will have access to the following benefits:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Competitive Pay Rates - &lt;/strong&gt;work this week, get paid next week!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;First choice of shifts at your Trust&lt;/strong&gt; – Access to shifts before they are available to agency&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Flexible working to suit your lifestyle &lt;/strong&gt;– Take control of when you want to work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Build holiday allowance for every shift you work &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Book and manage your shifts on the go&lt;/strong&gt; – Access shifts anywhere, anytime online or through your smartphone&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Support when you need it – 24/7 365 days – &lt;/strong&gt;Call us anytime on 03332 407 552&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Stakeholder pension scheme &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
